Job Details
Description
The Financial Applications – Operations & Support group is looking to fill the position of Systems Analyst, whose primary responsibilities will be focused on support and maintenance of various financial business applications and their integrations.
Responsibilities
Perform research, development and testing for solutions and resolutions regarding business application functionality;
Work with and support/maintain COTS Business Financial systems;
Analyze and revise existing system logic difficulties and documentation as necessary;
Perform regular patching and/or testing of patches implemented against business applications and servers.
Build and develop application tables, panels, and reports within business applications and databases;
Ensure continued, uninterrupted service through identifying and resolving problems in a client/server environment.
Responsible for software integration, external interface development and technical documentation;
Formulates and defines system scope and objectives through research and fact-finding to develop or modify moderately complex information systems;
In collaboration with the project team, document the applications and interventions in accordance with established standards;
Collaborate with third parties and internal team to configure secure communication, IP whitelisting, VPN tunnels, PGP configuration as well as the creation and maintenance of certificates.
Troubleshoot and resolve issues;
Provide support for the Company’s business applications, including periodic on-call support;
Analyze and follow service calls through to resolution using the incident management tool;
Requirements
Senior application professional with experience in monitoring, configuring and documenting, troubleshooting, and maintaining business applications;
Development expertise in integration platform tools such as Microsoft Logic Apps, Data Factory, API Manager Azure Functions, DevOps and Key Vault;
Knowledge of SOAP and REST web services;
Experience with integrating cloud based (Software as a Service) digital solutions;
Knowledge of OS and application layer patching;
Knowledge of server and business applications configuration and implementation/migration;
Knowledge of server and desktop processing/operating systems (Microsoft);
Excellent working knowledge of relational databases such as MS SQL Server and Oracle, including designing and tuning stored procedures;
Good working knowledge of formal change management processes;
Knowledge of ITIL framework would be considered an asset;
Experience providing 2nd – 3rd level application support for requests, incidents and problems in a Windows environment;
Experience in root cause analysis and providing workarounds and solutions for custom coded applications as well as commercial software;
Experience in using software tools/utilities to manage support/service calls and problems;
Strong planning, prioritizing and time management skills - must be able to undertake and manage multiple tasks at the same time and work under deadlines and operational pressures;
Strong analytical skills and critical thinking;
Knowledge of Sarbanes-Oxley requirements would be considered an asset;
Bilingualism (French and English) would be considered an asset;
Experience in PowerShell, REXX and VB scripting would be considered an asset;
Good understanding of purpose and definition of AD group policies;
Demonstrated knowledge and experience in defining and maintaining integration principles, patterns and standards, and providing integration services for digital solutions.
Demonstrated experience in delivering application and data integration solutions, including analysis, design, implementation and transition to support.
Demonstrated experience in maintaining an integration platform and process in production and non-production environments.
This is an in-office position in our Gatineau, Quebec location
Qualifications
University or College Degree in Computer Science/Technology or equivalent;
Two to five years’ experience as a systems analyst, Integration Specialist and/or system administrator.
